      What's this all about?
    %table{:style => "width:1120px;"}
      %tr
        %td{:style => "text-align:justify;vertical-align:top;", :width => "80%"}
          %p.small
            This summer we are going to make better open source, civic software together. Empty issues lists. Submit and merge pull requests. Make code easier to re-use and re-deploy.
          %img{:src => "/assets/tgach-ndoch/github-commits.png"}
          %h2 How it works
          %p.small
            All repos that close the issues identified at the beginning of the campaign will receive a Silver Fork Award: Code for America's recognition for civic hacking. Other Silver Fork Awards will be given for:
          %ul.small{:style => "padding-left:10px;"}
            %li
              Most merged pull requests
            %li
              Most issues closed
            %li
              Most contributors
            %li
              and others
          %h2 Calling Brigade
          %p.medium
            %a{:href => "https://docs.google.com/document/d/1QcUrUcAHu8eYXdLT7VeX0uLBlkKdCRKwWKYnoyN63qY/edit?usp=sharing"}Learn about the featured repos.
            %br
            Fork 'em.
            %br
            Close issues.
            %br
            Issue pulls.
            %br
            %img{:src => "http://i0.kym-cdn.com/photos/images/newsfeed/000/162/317/2vA1a.png?1313349760", :width => "100", :height => "300"}
            %p.small
              %img{:width => "70%", :src => "http://hackforchange.org/profiles/opencivic/themes/hackathon/logo.png"}
            %p.small
              June 1 was
              %a{:href => "http://hackforchange.org/"} National Day of Civic Hacking.
              Don't let it end there. Add your GitHub or Drupal.org orgs and repos and make a commitment to keep calm and hack on.
            %p.small
              Even better, since Hack for Change is
              %a{:href => "http://www.whitehouse.gov/blog/2013/01/22/roll-your-sleeves-get-involved-and-get-civic-hacking", :target => "top"} sponsored by The White House
              this an opportunity for your contributions to The Great American Civic Hack to be recognized on a national stage.
            %h2
              Introducing the Silver Fork Awards
            %p.small
              The Silver Fork Awards are Code for America Brigade's recognitions for civic hacking. We're going to track Brigade's extended network of civic hackers this summer and make leader boards for stuff like "Merged pull requests", "Issues closed"  and "Members Added". <span class="mini-icon  mini-icon-merge"></span><span class="mini-icon  mini-icon-issue-closed"></span> <span class="mini-icon  mini-icon-member-added"></span> There will be winning repos, repo managers and contributors.
